---
id: org.dxos.plugin.code
name: CodePlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A plugin for AI-assisted Composer plugin development. Hosts authored DEUS specs
(`.mdl` files), couples them to a `CodeProject`, and provides a Coder blueprint
that lets the assistant verify a spec, write source files into the project,
and (eventually) dispatch a build agent. The build/sandbox itself is a
separate EDGE service (out of scope until phase 2).

Phase 1 shipped: rename, schema, blueprint scaffold, settings, credential
wiring, and stub `verifySpec` / `runBuildAgent` operations.

Phase 1.5 (this PR) adds an in-memory CRUD surface for source files. The agent
can scaffold a project, list/read/write/delete files, and call the
`introspect-mcp` server to look up DXOS / Composer APIs. All file state is
ECHO-canonical — there is no sandbox or build runtime yet. The CodeArticle
renders a file tree alongside a CodeMirror editor (via `react-ui-editor`'s
`Editor.Root`) so a human can see what the agent is producing.

The plugin reuses `react-ui-editor`'s `Editor.Root` / `Editor.Toolbar` /
`Editor.Content` together with the existing `mdl()` CodeMirror extensions
instead of a bespoke editor implementation.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

```mdl
type Spec
  desc: |
    A DEUS spec document. Carries `.mdl` content and a human-readable name.
    Existing typename `org.dxos.type.spec` is preserved across the rename.
  fields:
    name?: string
    content: Ref<Text>          # mdl source
```

```mdl
type CodeProject
  desc: |
    A coding project. Pairs a name with a Spec used to drive code generation
    and the set of TypeScript source files that compose the plugin.
    Typename `org.dxos.type.codeProject`.
  fields:
    name?: string
    spec: Ref<Spec>             # the DEUS spec authored for this project
    files?: Ref<SourceFile>[]   # source tree, hierarchy implicit in path
```

```mdl
type SourceFile
  desc: |
    A single file in a CodeProject. The path is POSIX-style with folder
    separators ("src/components/Button.tsx"); folder objects are not modeled
    explicitly. `content` references a Text object so edits flow through ECHO
    reactivity and CRDT conflict resolution.
    Typename `org.dxos.type.sourceFile`.
  fields:
    path: string                # e.g. "src/plugin.ts"
    content: Ref<Text>
    mode?: number               # POSIX file mode; reserved for future use
```

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: |
    Plugin settings (plugin-scoped, not per-space). Reactive.
    The Anthropic API key itself is NOT stored here — it lives in an
    AccessToken ECHO object with source `anthropic.com`, accessed via
    the composer credentials API.
  fields:
    endpoint?: string           # URL of the EDGE build service (phase-2 wiring)
```

## Components

```mdl
component CodeArticle
  desc: |
    Article surface for a CodeProject. Two-pane layout: the left pane is a
    FileTree built from `project.files`, the right pane is a `react-ui-editor`
    `Editor.Root` bound to the selected SourceFile's `content` Text. Selecting
    a file in the tree replaces the editor's extensions to pick up the right
    language (`javascript({ typescript: true })` for .ts/.tsx, `markdown()`
    for .md, plain text otherwise). Edits flow through `createDataExtensions`
    so the underlying ECHO Text is updated reactively.
  props:
    role: string
    subject: CodeProject
    attendableId?: string
  state:
    selectedPath?: string
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────┬──────────────────────────┐
    │ FileTree     │ Editor.View              │
    │  package.json│   (lang based on path)   │
    │  ▾ src/      │                          │
    │    plugin.ts │                          │
    │  README.md   │                          │
    └──────────────┴──────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component FileTree
  desc: |
    Renders a flat list of SourceFile-style entries as a hierarchical tree.
    Folders are derived from path components and rendered as collapsible
    nodes; clicking a leaf calls `onSelect`. Pure component — no ECHO
    awareness — to keep storybook coverage simple.
  props:
    files: { path: string }[]
    selectedPath?: string
    onSelect?: (path: string) => void
    emptyMessage?: string
```

```mdl
component SpecArticle
  desc: |
    Article surface for a bare Spec. Uses `react-ui-editor`'s Editor primitives
    with the existing `mdl()` / `mdlBlockDescription` / `mdlLint` /
    `mdlComplete` CodeMirror extensions for `.mdl` syntax, lint, completion.
  props:
    role: string
    subject: Spec
    attendableId?: string
```

```mdl
component CodeSettings
  desc: |
    Settings surface contributed via `AppPlugin.addSettingsModule`. Lets the
    user paste/clear an Anthropic API key. The key is persisted to an
    AccessToken (source `anthropic.com`) in the user's HALO space; reads/
    writes go through the composer credentials API, not Settings.
  props:
    settings: Settings
  state:
    apiKey?: string             # bound to AccessToken.token
  actions:
    saveApiKey(value: string)
    clearApiKey()
```

## Services

```mdl
service Credentials
  desc: |
    Composer credentials API (`@dxos/functions/services/CredentialsService`).
    Used by `CodeSettings` to read/write the Anthropic API key as an
    AccessToken with source `anthropic.com`.
  ops:
    getCredential(query: { service: string }) → ServiceCredential
    queryCredentials(query: { service: string }) → ServiceCredential[]
```

```mdl
service BuildAgent
  desc: |
    The remote EDGE service that runs the Claude Agent SDK to generate
    Composer plugins from a Spec. Out of scope for this PR — phase 1 only
    declares the contract surface. Will live in `dxos/edge`.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    verify(spec: Spec) → { ok: bool, messages: string[] }
    build(project: CodeProject) → { runId: string, status: string }
```

## Operations

Phase-1 ops (`verifySpec`, `runBuildAgent`) are stubs until the EDGE build
service exists. Phase-1.5 adds real handlers for file CRUD over ECHO; no
sandbox is involved.

```mdl
op verifySpec
  desc: |
    Static verification of a DEUS spec — lint + structural checks. Phase-1
    stub returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`. Will eventually delegate to
    BuildAgent.verify.
  input:
    spec: Ref<Spec>
  output: { ok: bool, messages: string[] }
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Operation key: `org.dxos.function.code.verify-spec`.
    Exposed as a blueprint tool on CoderBlueprint.
```

```mdl
op runBuildAgent
  desc: |
    Dispatches a build of the project via the EDGE BuildAgent. Phase-1 stub
    returns `{ status: "queued" }` without performing any work.
  input:
    project: Ref<CodeProject>
  output: { status: queued | running | succeeded | failed }
  effects: [echo:read, http]
  requires: [Database, Credentials]
  note: |
    Operation key: `org.dxos.function.code.run-build-agent`.
    Phase-2: reads the Anthropic API key via Credentials and POSTs to the
    EDGE BuildAgent endpoint configured in Settings.endpoint.
```

```mdl
op listFiles
  desc: List the source files in a CodeProject (path + size).
  input:  { project: Ref<CodeProject> }
  output: { files: { path: string, size: number }[] }
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note:   Operation key `org.dxos.function.code.list-files`.
```

```mdl
op readFile
  desc: Read the content of a single file in a CodeProject.
  input:  { project: Ref<CodeProject>, path: string }
  output: { path: string, content: string }
  errors: [FileNotFound]
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note:   Operation key `org.dxos.function.code.read-file`.
```

```mdl
op writeFile
  desc: |
    Create or overwrite a file in a CodeProject. Whole-file write — for
    targeted edits, prefer reading first and writing back the new content.
    Returns `created: true` for new files, `created: false` for overwrites.
  input:  { project: Ref<CodeProject>, path: string, content: string }
  output: { path: string, created: boolean }
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [Database]
  note:   Operation key `org.dxos.function.code.write-file`.
```

```mdl
op deleteFile
  desc: Remove a file from a CodeProject by path.
  input:  { project: Ref<CodeProject>, path: string }
  output: { path: string, deleted: boolean }
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [Database]
  note:   Operation key `org.dxos.function.code.delete-file`.
```

```mdl
op scaffoldProject
  desc: |
    Seed a CodeProject with a minimal Composer plugin scaffold
    (package.json, src/plugin.ts, README.md). Idempotent — overwrites any
    files at the scaffold paths but never deletes user files.
  input:  { project: Ref<CodeProject>, name?: string }
  output: { files: { path: string, size: number }[] }
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [Database]
  note:   Operation key `org.dxos.function.code.scaffold`.
```

## Blueprints

```mdl
type CoderBlueprint
  desc: |
    Blueprint key `org.dxos.blueprint.coder`. Drives plugin authoring:
    iterate on the Spec with the user, look up DXOS / Composer APIs through
    introspect-mcp, scaffold the project, then write/read/delete source
    files until the user is satisfied.
  fields:
    key: org.dxos.blueprint.coder
    tools:
      - op:verifySpec
      - op:runBuildAgent
      - op:listFiles
      - op:readFile
      - op:writeFile
      - op:deleteFile
      - op:scaffoldProject
    mcpServers:
      - introspect-mcp        # remote MCP, http; tools: list_packages,
                              # get_package, list_symbols, find_symbol,
                              # get_symbol
    instructions: prose
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Rename plugin-spec → plugin-code

  req F-1.1: Package renamed `@dxos/plugin-spec` → `@dxos/plugin-code`.
  req F-1.2: Directory renamed `packages/plugins/plugin-spec` → `packages/plugins/plugin-code`.
  req F-1.3: Plugin id renamed `org.dxos.plugin.spec` → `org.dxos.plugin.code`.
  req F-1.4: SpecPlugin → CodePlugin; SpecArticle → CodeArticle.
  req F-1.5: Spec ECHO type retains typename `org.dxos.type.spec` (no migration).
  req F-1.6:
    when: composer-app loads after rename
    then: existing Spec objects continue to render; no schema migration needed
```

```mdl
feat F-2: CodeProject type

  req F-2.1: New ECHO type `CodeProject` with typename `org.dxos.type.codeProject`.
  req F-2.2: Fields `name?: string`, `spec: Ref<Spec>`; both reactive.
  req F-2.3:
    when: user creates a CodeProject from the navtree
    then: an empty Spec is created and referenced by the new CodeProject
  req F-2.4: CodeProject registered via `addSchemaModule` and `addMetadataModule`.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: CodeArticle uses react-ui-editor

  req F-3.1: CodeArticle uses `Editor.Root` + `Editor.Toolbar` + `Editor.Content`
             from `@dxos/react-ui-editor` instead of a bespoke `useTextEditor` setup.
  req F-3.2: The existing `mdl()`, `mdlBlockDescription`, `mdlLint`, `mdlComplete`
             extensions are passed to the editor.
  req F-3.3:
    when: a Spec is opened
    then: its `content` is editable with markdown + .mdl block highlighting
  req F-3.4: Toolbar exposes a Spec | Code tab toggle via `customActions`.
  req F-3.5:
    when: user clicks "Code"
    then: editor area is hidden and a placeholder ("Build output will appear here") is shown
  req F-3.6:
    when: user clicks "Spec"
    then: editor area is restored and focus returns to the document
  req F-3.7: Active tab is local component state (not persisted).
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Settings + credentials

  req F-4.1: `Settings` schema mutable, with optional `endpoint: string`.
  req F-4.2: Settings registered via `AppPlugin.addSettingsModule`.
  req F-4.3: A `CodeSettings` container renders an API-key input.
  req F-4.4:
    when: user enters an API key and saves
    then: an `AccessToken` is upserted with `source: "anthropic.com"`, `token: <value>`
          via the composer credentials API
  req F-4.5:
    when: user clears the key
    then: the matching AccessToken is removed
  req F-4.6: API key value is never stored in `Settings`.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Coder blueprint

  req F-5.1: A blueprint with key `org.dxos.blueprint.coder` is contributed
             via `addBlueprintDefinitionModule`.
  req F-5.2: Tools include op:verifySpec and op:runBuildAgent.
  req F-5.3: System instructions describe the Coder role:
              author/refine spec with user, run verifySpec, then runBuildAgent.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Stub operations

  req F-6.1: op:verifySpec defined and handler returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`.
  req F-6.2: op:runBuildAgent defined and handler returns `{ status: "queued" }`.
  req F-6.3: Both handlers are contributed via `addOperationHandlerModule`.
  req F-6.4: Both operations resolve from blueprint tool calls without error.
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Source files in ECHO

  req F-7.1: New ECHO type SourceFile with typename `org.dxos.type.sourceFile`.
  req F-7.2: CodeProject extended with optional `files: Ref<SourceFile>[]`.
  req F-7.3: SourceFile registered via `addSchemaModule` and translations.
  req F-7.4:
    when: a SourceFile is mutated through write-file
    then: the underlying Text object is updated; the file Ref already in
          `project.files` is reused (no duplicate file objects per path).
  req F-7.5:
    when: a path that doesn't yet exist is written
    then: a new SourceFile + Text are created and appended to `project.files`.
```

```mdl
feat F-8: File CRUD operations

  req F-8.1: op:listFiles returns the project's files sorted by path.
  req F-8.2: op:readFile resolves a file by exact-path match and returns its content.
  req F-8.3:
    when: op:readFile is called with an unknown path
    then: the operation fails with a FileNotFound error
  req F-8.4: op:writeFile creates new files and overwrites existing ones (whole-file).
  req F-8.5: op:deleteFile removes the matching file from `project.files`.
  req F-8.6: op:scaffoldProject seeds package.json, src/plugin.ts, README.md and
             returns the resulting file list.
  req F-8.7: All file ops are wired into the CoderBlueprint tool set.
```

```mdl
feat F-9: CodeArticle file tree + editor

  req F-9.1: CodeArticle renders a two-pane layout: FileTree on the left,
             editor on the right.
  req F-9.2: FileTree is a pure component (no ECHO awareness) and is unit-
             coverable from a Storybook story.
  req F-9.3: Selecting a file replaces the editor's language extension based
             on the file's extension (`.ts`/`.tsx` → typescript JS, `.md` →
             markdown, otherwise plain JS).
  req F-9.4: The editor is `react-ui-editor`'s `Editor.Root` with
             `createDataExtensions` so edits propagate back into the
             SourceFile's Text via ECHO.
  req F-9.5:
    when: the agent writes a new file via op:writeFile
    then: the file appears in the FileTree on the next render
  req F-9.6:
    when: `project.files` is empty
    then: an empty-state message points the user at the Coder agent
```

```mdl
feat F-10: Coder integrates introspect-mcp

  req F-10.1: CoderBlueprint declares a remote MCP server entry pointing at the
              introspect-mcp HTTP endpoint.
  req F-10.2: System prompt directs the agent to call introspect-mcp
              (find_symbol / get_symbol / list_packages …) before writing
              code that touches DXOS / Composer APIs.
  req F-10.3:
    when: introspect-mcp is unreachable
    then: chat continues to function (per @dxos/plugin-assistant resilience);
          the agent simply has no API search tools available.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Rename preserves Spec compatibility
  given: a space already containing a Spec object created by plugin-spec
  when: the renamed plugin-code is loaded
  then:
    - the Spec object is queryable
    - opening it renders CodeArticle with the same content
    - typename remains `org.dxos.type.spec`
```

```mdl
test T-2: Create CodeProject
  given: composer-app with plugin-code loaded
  when: user invokes "Create CodeProject" from a space
  then:
    - a new CodeProject object is created with default name
    - a new empty Spec is created and referenced via `project.spec`
    - opening the project surfaces the linked Spec via CodeArticle
```

```mdl
test T-3: Editor renders mdl content
  given: a Spec containing an mdl fenced block
  when: CodeArticle mounts
  then:
    - markdown is decorated by `decorateMarkdown()`
    - the mdl block body is highlighted by `mdlBlockDescription`
    - lint and completion sources are wired
```

```mdl
test T-4: Toolbar tab toggle
  given: a CodeArticle is open showing the Spec view
  when: user clicks the Code tab
  then:
    - the editor content is hidden
    - the Code placeholder ("Build output will appear here") is visible
  when: user clicks the Spec tab
  then: the editor content is visible again
```

```mdl
test T-5: Save API key persists AccessToken
  given: CodeSettings is open and no AccessToken exists for `anthropic.com`
  when: user enters a key and clicks save
  then:
    - an AccessToken with `source: "anthropic.com"` and the entered token is created
    - the input shows the masked persisted value on next render
```

```mdl
test T-6: Clear API key removes AccessToken
  given: an AccessToken exists for `anthropic.com`
  when: user clicks clear
  then:
    - the AccessToken is removed
    - subsequent `CredentialsService.getCredential({ service: "anthropic.com" })` rejects
```

```mdl
test T-7: Blueprint registers tools
  given: composer-app with plugin-code loaded
  when: AppCapabilities.BlueprintDefinition is queried for `org.dxos.blueprint.coder`
  then:
    - the blueprint is present
    - its tool set includes verifySpec and runBuildAgent
```

```mdl
test T-8: Stub operations resolve
  given: an assistant chat with the Coder blueprint loaded
  when: the assistant invokes verifySpec on a Spec
  then: the call returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`
  when: the assistant invokes runBuildAgent on a CodeProject
  then: the call returns `{ status: "queued" }`
```

```mdl
test T-9: Scaffold seeds project files
  given: an empty CodeProject
  when: op:scaffoldProject is invoked with name "demo"
  then:
    - `project.files` includes SourceFiles at paths package.json, src/plugin.ts, README.md
    - each file's Text content is non-empty and reflects the project name
```

```mdl
test T-10: Round-trip read/write/delete
  given: a CodeProject with one file at "src/foo.ts"
  when: op:writeFile is called with path "src/foo.ts" and content "X"
  then: op:readFile returns content "X" and `created: false`
  when: op:writeFile is called with path "src/bar.ts" and content "Y"
  then: op:readFile returns content "Y" and `created: true`
  when: op:deleteFile is called with path "src/bar.ts"
  then: op:listFiles no longer reports "src/bar.ts"
```

```mdl
test T-11: CodeArticle reflects ECHO mutations
  given: a CodeArticle is mounted on a CodeProject
  when: a new SourceFile is added to `project.files` via op:writeFile
  then: the FileTree shows the new path on next render without manual reload
```

```mdl
test T-12: Coder blueprint exposes file tools
  given: composer-app with plugin-code loaded
  when: AppCapabilities.BlueprintDefinition is queried for `org.dxos.blueprint.coder`
  then:
    - the blueprint's tool set includes listFiles, readFile, writeFile,
      deleteFile, and scaffoldProject
    - the blueprint declares an introspect-mcp remote MCP server
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
